:::{{DIcon|Talk}} What's a nymph?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_401555104-->
::::'''Prototype Garmentmaker:''' That's a little complicated. In short, nymphs were essentially... human beings who had lived in the Era Chrysea.
::::'''Prototype Garmentmaker:''' Legend has it that Thanatos sent disciples of Romance to defective cocoons, where they were reborn as butterflies, destined to continue their lives as loyal aides to the Titan.
::::'''Prototype Garmentmaker:''' In the Era Bellica, {{Rubi|Cerces|Reason Titan}} accidentally lost their divine form. {{Rubi|Mnestia|Romance Titan}}, unable to accept the fact that their lover was injured, collected Cerces' scattered bodies, intending to weave them together with threads to bring them back.
::::'''Prototype Garmentmaker:''' The former followers of the two also voluntarily joined this arduous journey, and they are the Creation Nymphs. The beautiful and fragile belong to Mnestia, while the brave and strong belong to Cerces.
::::'''Prototype Garmentmaker:''' Reassembling a divine body is no easy task. The nymph must perceive all things, gathering wisdom and love from the words of others to provide for Mnestia's weaving of the golden threads. Thus, they have an alternate name: "Weavers."
::::'''Prototype Garmentmaker:''' But this act... is destined to be futile.
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} How does a nymph assist you?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_401555109-->
::::'''Prototype Garmentmaker:''' As karma has been severed in the current era, the benediction bestowed upon the nymph becomes incredibly precious. If gathered to form a mountain, these benedictions would hold enough power to break even the most unyielding seal.
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Will they agree to it?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_401555114-->
::::'''Prototype Garmentmaker:''' We are all connected to Mnestia in one way or another. Once the reasons are articulated, I believe many will be eager to contribute. After all, this prophecy concerns the Titans themselves.
::::'''Prototype Garmentmaker:''' Once I have their approval, I'll arrange for their memories and souls, binding their benedictions together with the golden thread... Let's hope this truly succeeds.
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} Are all the nymphs I found here?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_304006002-->
::::'''Prototype Garmentmaker:''' Yes, the blessings of these nymphs have been extracted by golden needles. To avoid harming their souls, I crafted special insect bodies sewn from the golden threads, allowing them to temporarily reside within.
::::'''Prototype Garmentmaker:''' The nymphs are my assistants, my messengers, my eyes. We share the title of "Weavers," an inseparable bond. If possible, I hope the holy city can provide them sanctuary as well.
::::'''Prototype Garmentmaker:''' In the past, nymphs made their home within the "Cocoon of Romance," where they exchanged fascinating secrets. Mnestia's silk threads allowed them to evade the call of the River of Souls, like sailors crossing the sea on a vessel.
::::'''Prototype Garmentmaker:''' I lived through an era when "Romance" was yet untainted and knew the cocoon's structure. Thus, I attempted to replicate that shelter for them using the golden threads &mdash; what you see now as these insect bodies.
::::'''Prototype Garmentmaker:''' Though only a temporary measure, it's enough to sustain them until the end of the Flame-Chase Journey.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: ALL_TALK_END-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: ALL_TALK_END-->
:::<!--Ends the current performance-->
